%include	/usr/lib/rpm/macros.perl
%define	pdir	Class
%define	pnam	MethodMaker
Summary:	Class::MethodMaker - a module for creating generic methods
#Summary(pl):	
Name:		perl-%{pdir}-%{pnam}
Version:	1.06
Release:	1
License:	GPL/Artistic
Group:		Development/Languages/Perl
Source0:	ftp://ftp.cpan.org/pub/CPAN/modules/by-module/%{pdir}/%{pdir}-%{pnam}-%{version}.tar.gz
BuildRequires:	perl >= 5.6
BuildRequires:	rpm-perlprov >= 3.0.3-26
BuildRequires:	perl-modules
BuildArch:	noarch
BuildRoot:	%{tmpdir}/%{name}-%{version}-root-%(id -u -n)

%description
This module solves the problem of having to write a bazillion get/set
methods that are all the same.  The argument to 'use' is a hash whose
keys are the names of types of generic methods generated by MethodMaker
and whose values tell method maker what methods to make.  (More precisely,
the keys are the names of MethodMaker methods (methods that write methods)
and the values are the arguments to those methods.

